\date{2025-02-03}
\title{Suspension}
\taxon{construction}


\p{
The suspension of a type #{A} is given by the pushout of #{(\top \xleftarrow{!} A \xrightarrow{!} \top)}.
}

\subtree{
\taxon{remark}
\p{
 The universal property of [pushouts](ca-0002) says that maps out of the suspension: #{\Sigma A \to B} corresponds to pairs of points in #{B} with a function from #{A} into paths between them.
 ##{
  (\Sigma A \to B) \xrightarrow{\sim} (\Sigma_{(a,b : B)} (A \to a = b))
 }
}
}